\frac d{dx} y(x)
\begin{align*} \frac d{dx} \sqrt{y^2(x)+1} & = \frac1{2\sqrt{y^2(x)+1}} \cdot \frac d{dx} (y^2(x) + 1) \\ & = \frac1{2\sqrt{y^2(x)+1}} 2y(x) \cdot y'(x) \\ & \stackrel{\text{ODE}}= \frac1{\sqrt{y^2(x)+1}} \cdot y(x) \cdot \sqrt{y^2(x)+1} \\ & = y(x) \end{align*}
\frac{d^{2}y}{dx^2} = \left( \frac{dy}{dx}\right)'
\frac{dy}{dx}
x
